Linux Deep Dive Cheat Sheet for DevOps Interviews
Networking & Ports
Check open ports on local machine:
ss -tuln
ss -tulpn
netstat -tulpn
lsof -i -P -n | grep LISTEN
Check if remote port is accessible:
nc -zv <host> <port>
nc -zv -w 3 <host> <port>
curl -I http://<host>:<port>
telnet <host> <port>
nmap -p <port> <host>
Disk & Filesystem
Check free disk space:
df -h
df -Th
df --total -h
Check free inodes:
df -i
Disk usage by directory:
du -sh *
du -sh /var/log/*
Find large files:
find / -type f -size +500M 2>/dev/null
System Resource Usage
CPU, memory, processes:
top
htop
ps aux --sort=-%cpu
ps aux --sort=-%mem
Memory usage:
free -h
vmstat 1 5
Load average:
uptime
cat /proc/loadavg
Logs & Monitoring
Tail logs:
tail -f /var/log/syslog
Linux Deep Dive Cheat Sheet for DevOps Interviews
tail -n 100 /var/log/messages
Search inside logs:
grep "ERROR" /var/log/syslog
grep -i "fail" /var/log/auth.log
grep -R "keyword" /path/to/dir
Follow logs with filters:
tail -f /var/log/syslog | grep "WARN"
File & Directory Operations
Find files:
find / -name "filename"
find /etc -type f -name "*.conf"
Find by modified time:
find /var/log -type f -mtime -1
Permissions & ownership:
ls -l
chmod 644 file
chmod +x script.sh
chown user:group file
Services
Check service status:
systemctl status ssh
systemctl is-active ssh
systemctl is-enabled ssh
Start/stop/restart:
sudo systemctl restart nginx
Networking Configuration
Show IP address:
ip a
hostname -I
Routing table:
ip route
DNS resolution:
nslookup example.com
dig example.com
Connectivity:
ping -c 4 google.com
traceroute google.com
Linux Deep Dive Cheat Sheet for DevOps Interviews
mtr google.com
User & Permission Management
id
whoami
who
w
last
sudo -l
User management:
sudo useradd -m username
sudo passwd username
sudo userdel -r username
Package Management
Debian/Ubuntu:
sudo apt update
sudo apt install package
dpkg -l | grep package
RHEL/CentOS:
sudo yum install package
rpm -qa | grep package
Process & Job Management
ps -ef | grep process
kill <pid>
kill -9 <pid>
jobs
fg %1
bg %1
File Transfer
scp file user@host:/path
rsync -avz file user@host:/path
wget URL
curl -O URL
Compression & Archiving
tar -czvf archive.tar.gz folder/
tar -xzvf archive.tar.gz
zip -r archive.zip folder/
unzip archive.zip
SELinux & Firewall
Linux Deep Dive Cheat Sheet for DevOps Interviews
sestatus
getenforce
setenforce 0
UFW firewall:
sudo ufw status
sudo ufw allow 22
sudo ufw deny 80
Firewalld:
sudo firewall-cmd --state
sudo firewall-cmd --list-all
Misc. Admin
Check system uptime:
uptime
Kernel & OS version:
uname -a
cat /etc/os-release
Check last reboot:
who -b
One-Liner Troubleshooting
Find top 10 biggest files:
find / -type f -exec du -Sh {} + 2>/dev/null | sort -rh | head -n 10
Check if specific port is listening:
ss -tulpn | grep :80
Check process holding a port:
lsof -i :443
Check failed login attempts:
grep "Failed password" /var/log/auth.log